race.comment: TULONG (4) is third up and finds a winnable assignment. Didn't have the best of it early on over this trip at the Sunshine Coast 12 days ago as a $2.8F. Maps well and the in-form Maloney sticking aboard is a decent push for his chances. HARD AS BROK (6) went close at Doomben before the spell but has lacked finishing dash at Doomben both starts this preparation. He'll appreciate the step up to the mile and Ben Thompson has been booked by the Vandyke yard. WILY JACK (8) raced favourite at the Gold Coast second-up over 1400m and didn't enjoy the best of luck placing second behind a dominant winner. The mile will suit and he can make the finish. AVERRED (1) resumed with a narrow defeat at the Sunshine Coast and then went back and settled a long way from the action. Has a low gate today and the handy 3kg claim and is likely to show more at odds.
